<h1><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Where to find supplies in town</span></h1><p>Places that you can find supplies through the university:</p><p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Nightline&nbsp;</span>37 Old Elvet, DH1 3HN&nbsp;</strong>(behind the Dun Cow pub)&nbsp;<br /><br /></p><p>Provide: <span style="color: #051a83;">Safe-sex supplies<strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;</strong></span>condoms, lube and dental dams free of charge to Durham students.<strong>&nbsp;</strong><span style="color: #051a83;">Attack alarms -&nbsp;</span>If you are feeling unsafe about walking about at night, Nightline can lend you an attack alarm.&nbsp;<span style="color: #051a83;">Pregnancy tests -&nbsp;</span>Nightline provides anonymous and confidential pregnancy tests free of charge.&nbsp;<span style="color: #051a83;">Chlamydia screening -</span>There is an ongoing Chlamydia screening programme available to anyone under the age of 25 in County Durham and Darlington. Urine samples can be sent off by post to a clinic in Darlington where they are tested. Nightline has a supply of these screening packs.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Nightline run 9pm to 7am during term-time and you can drop in to collect any of these supplies.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Students' Union</span></strong>&nbsp;Advice and Help Service<strong>&nbsp;Dunelm House,&nbsp;</strong><strong>New Elvet, DH1 3AN</strong></p><p><strong><img src="http://community.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/welfare/img/upload/001.jpg" alt="" /></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">University Health Centre</span><br />The practice nurses provide contraceptive advice and services, including the morning after pill, as well as chlamydia screening and pregnancy testing.&nbsp;</p><p>Condoms (free of charge) are available from reception without an appointment.&nbsp;</p><p>For more information on the health centre generally follow this link:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.durhamstudenthealth.co.uk">http://www.durhamstudenthealth.co.uk</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2>In Town&nbsp;</h2><h3>Boots the Chemists</h3><p>&bull; Free emergency contraception (depending on pharmacist on duty).</p><p>&bull; C-Card condom distribution.</p><p>&bull; Self-take urine Chlamydia screening for under 25s (see www.haveigotit.org for more info and details of other locations).</p><p>2/5 The Market Place<br />Durham<br />County Durham<br />DH1 3NB</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3>Boots the Chemists</h3><p>&bull; Free emergency contraception (depending on pharmacist on duty).&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; C-Card condom distribution.&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Self-take urine Chlamydia screening for under 25s (see www.haveigotit.org for more info and details of other locations).</p><div class="fcdetailsleft"><p class="fcaddress">6 North Road<br />Durham<br />County Durham<br />DH1 4SH&nbsp;</p><p class="fcaddress">&nbsp;</p></div><h3 class="fcdetailsright">The Co-Operative Pharmacy</h3><div class="fcdetailsright">&bull; Free emergency contraception (depending on pharmacist on duty).&nbsp;</div><div class="fcdetailsright">&nbsp;</div><div class="fcdetailsright">25 Gilesgate<br />Durham<br />County Durham<br />DH1 1QW&nbsp;</div><div class="fcdetailsright">&nbsp;</div><h3 class="fcdetailsright">The Venue (Durham City Centre Youth Project)</h3><div class="fcdetailsright">&bull;&nbsp;Registration and distribution point for the C-Card free condom distribution scheme.</div><div class="fcdetailsright">&nbsp;</div><div class="fcdetailsright">27 North Road<br />Durham<br />County Durham<br />DH1 4SG&nbsp;</div><div class="fcdetailsright">&nbsp;</div><h3 class="fcdetailsright">CASH Clinic - St Margaret's Health Centre</h3><div class="fcdetailsright">&bull; Contraceptives&nbsp;<br />&bull; Emergency contraception&nbsp;<br />&bull; Pregnancy testing&nbsp;<br />&bull; Chlamydia screening&nbsp;<br />&bull; Sexually Transmitted Infections testing&nbsp;<br />&bull; Smear testing&nbsp;<br />&bull; Advice and referral for termination (women can also make their own referral on 01388 455333)&nbsp;<br />&bull; Registration and distribution point for C-Card condom scheme</div><div class="fcdetailsright">&nbsp;</div><div class="fcdetailsright">Crossgate<br />Durham<br />County Durham<br />DH1 4DS&nbsp;</div><div class="fcdetailsright">&nbsp;</div><h3 class="fcdetailsright">M Whitfield Pharmacy</h3><div class="fcdetailsright"><p>&bull; Free emergency contraception (depending on pharmacist on duty).&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; C-Card condom distribution.&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Self-take urine Chlamydia screening for under 25s (see www.haveigotit.org for more info and details of other locations).</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>34 Sunderland Road<br />Durham<br />County Durham<br />DH1 2LG&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3>GUM Clinic - University Hospital of North Durham</h3><p>A discreet and confidential service is provided for those people requiring sexual health screening and advice. Anyone wishing to attend can make an appointment or attend and wait at a drop-in session directly without having seen a doctor or nurse elsewhere. The service includes diagnosis, treatment and management of sexually transmitted infections, including HIV and specialist dermatology clinics for skin related conditions. A full range of contraceptive methods is also available. Registration and distribution point for C-Card condom scheme. Telephone advice is provided by Health Advisers.</p><p>North Road</p><p>Durham</p><p>County Durham</p><p>DH1 5TW&nbsp;</p></div><p>&nbsp;</p><p>C-card information:&nbsp;</p><p><a href="http://www.cddft.nhs.uk/media/254118/c%20card%20leaflet.pdf">http://www.cddft.nhs.uk/media/254118/c%20card%20leaflet.pdf</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>